ODI Guinea-Bissau - (Visual) Exploratory Data Analysis¶

Glenn Abastillas | April 7, 2020

This notebook contains exploratory data analyses (EDA) on merged data from region shape files, COVID data, and Census data.

import pandas as pd
import geopandas as gpd
import numpy as np
import altair as alt
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import json

%matplotlib inline

Load Data¶

data = gpd.read_file('data/aux/merged.json')

Convert to GeoJSON¶

geojson = json.loads(data.to_json())
geojson = alt.Data(values=geojson['features'])

Basic Plot of Sectors and Regions¶

dim = {'width' : 800, 'height' : 600}
basic_plot = alt.Chart(geojson, **dim).mark_geoshape(stroke='black', strokeWidth=2)

Color by region and tooltip by sector.

selection = alt.selection_single(on='mouseover')

options = {
    'tooltip' : alt.Tooltip('properties.ADM1_NAME:N'),
    'color' : alt.Color('properties.ADM1_NAME:N', legend=alt.Legend(title='Region')),
    'opacity' : alt.condition(selection, alt.value(.7), alt.value(0.3))
}

basic_plot = basic_plot.encode(**options).add_selection(selection)
basic_plot

Basic Demographic Plot (2010 Population)¶

basic_pop = alt.Chart(geojson, **dim).mark_geoshape(stroke='black', strokeWidth=2)

options['color'] = alt.Color('properties.B_2010_E:Q', legend=alt.Legend(title='Population in 2010'))
options['tooltip'] = alt.Tooltip('properties.B_2010_E:Q')

basic_pop.encode(color=alt.value('gray')) + \
basic_pop.encode(**options).add_selection(selection)

Basic Demographic Plot (Age)¶

basic_age = alt.Chart(geojson, **dim).mark_geoshape(stroke='black', strokeWidth=2)

options['color'] = alt.Color('properties.A65PLUSB:Q', legend=alt.Legend(title='Age 65+ (ca. 2010)'))
options['tooltip'] = alt.Tooltip('properties.A65PLUSB:Q')

basic_age.encode(color=alt.value('gray')) + \
basic_age.encode(**options).add_selection(selection)
